---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="BridgeAIChat Claude Guide" description="Run Claude CLI behind BridgeAIChat with the right expectations for auth and quota.">
  <section class="surface">
    <div class="eyebrow">Tool Guide</div>
    <h1>Claude works, but device state matters.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      BridgeAIChat can call Claude CLI from the agent device, but the real runtime behavior still depends on whether
      that device is logged in and whether the account has quota remaining.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Before you test</div>
      <h2>Check the local device directly</h2>
      <pre>claude -p "hi"</pre>
      <p>If that command fails on the machine itself, BridgeAIChat will not be able to produce a successful reply through the agent either.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Common blockers</div>
      <h2>What usually goes wrong</h2>
      <ul class="list tight">
        <li>The device is not logged into Claude CLI</li>
        <li>The daily or hourly quota has been exhausted</li>
        <li>The configured command path does not match the installed Claude binary</li>
        <li>The user expects persistent Claude conversation state, but the beta path is still safer with one-shot calls</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
